<p><i>It’s okay to stay inside.</i></p>

<p><b>Reclaiming Solitude</b> is a short game about the benefits of slowing down and taking some time for yourself.</p>

<p>Read a good book. Listen to the radio. Enjoy a moment of solitude.</p>

<p>The game centres in on one room, with very limited space for the player to move, and time only moves when the player interacts with any of the objects in the room. Reclaiming Solitude came about during the first period of the COVID-19 lockdown, a time when a lot of my friends and colleagues were suffering from serious cabin fever. It’s partly a reminder to them about the benefits of relaxing indoors, partly a reminder to myself to relax more and work less (!) and partly a relaxing experience to hopefully take people’s minds off the pandemic.</p>

<p>Made in Bitsy for the ‘Isolation’ Bitsy game jam.</p>

